701578f-a.folder: Parkside Place & Webster Avenue, Bronx, NY
701578f-a.text:
(1)
Parkside Place (extreme left), west side, at its junction with Webster Ave. (at East 210th Street), showing excavation work in progress. The view is in a southerly direction from the Williamsbridge station (East 210th Street) of the Third Avenue Elevated Line.
May 25, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
Another view of the same. The frame houses, on the left, face on
the east side of Decatur Ave.
May 25, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
